<br>
    #1.  Improved Reclaim is the impetus for trying the tactic at all, as the mana recovery benefits are amazing.  This means you need to be 59+ to attempt it, and have a solid AA base (Spell Casting Mastery 3 is my suggestion).<br>
<br>
    #2.  Quick Summoning benefits this tactic greatly, as it gives you less chance of a root break interrupting your resummon.  Summoning Haste 3 also helps while you are still building AA points for QS.<br>
<br>
    #3.  Solo, it forces you to get in much closer to the mob than a caster might feel comfortable with.  You need to see the spell messages to see if root landed or not.<br>
<br>
    #4.  The risks associated with the tactic are greatly minimized with a second magician, as root breaks are inconsequential, and you can stand as far away as Reclaim Energy allows you (100 units, or more with an Extended Range item, just like a heal spell).<br>
<br>
    #5.  I strongly urge you to be spec conj 200, Spell Casting Mastery 3, and be wearing a Summoning Efficiency 3 item.  This will maximize the mana recovery involved in the tactic, allowing you to buff each and every pet without worrying about your mana pool.<br>
<br>
    The benefits of the tactic are great, but risk is there too.  This is truly living on the edge for Magician tactics.  Try it and decide for yourself, or read about it here.  Obviously this isn't for everyone.<br>
